At Syracuse tyranny became so intolerable after the death of Dion that the people summoned Timoleon from Corinth to restore good government. By a vig- orous attack he routed the tyrant and restored the old constitution of Syracuse ; then, with singular seli-abnegation laid down the power and ended his days as a private citizen.
